Defendant in custody on WRIT.   
Count 1 - Strangulation and suffocation (DVO) - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, battery (DVO).  Motion granted.   Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of thirty-six (36) months.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision concurrent with sentence defendant is currently serving from Shawano County Case No. 08 CF 115.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Complete any counseling the DOC suggests;
3) Maintain full-time employment or school or participate in a work search if unemployed;
4) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but not the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given credit for 81 days already served.  
